  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maria.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that's exactly what she said when she came to see me in Prague.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she said, I want you to use my flat as your home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I want you to come to Celakovice whenever you can.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it'll be your second home and you'll always be welcome.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had such a wonderful, bright, sunny nature, and such a warm heart.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was so wonderful to get out of the drab flat that auntie and I were living in-- or should I call it the drab room-- and have a couple of days also away from her, that I spent very many happy weekends with Maria.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when she told me one night that the sheets I was sleeping in between were bought and chosen by my mother, and the towel I was drying myself in were also from her, it made it all the more precious.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In fact, I never went back again to Prague without having something or other that was bought my mother in my little overnight bag.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] really [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] loved those-- those weekends.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Again, I kept feeling so much closer to my parents.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My sister followed a few months after me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But she only stayed a couple of months.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She just could not take it, could not take the country as it was, the harshness of it, of the post-war conditions, and also could not cope with the void the death of our parents had left, which was very, very hard to bear.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she returned back to Britain shortly before the coup d'etat, shortly before the communists-- communists took over.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
